# Figma Code Connect workflow

Code contracts for `components/ui/*` and `lib/design-system.ts` live in **`design-system-enforcement.mdc`**. This rule covers the **Figma↔code parity** workflow specifically.

## Primitive API change checklist

When changing a primitive in `components/ui/*`:

1. Keep variant names identical between Figma and code — normalize code first if they diverge.
2. Keep slot names aligned to `data-slot` anatomy (do not rename slots without updating Figma / Code Connect artifacts).
3. Update **Figma Code Connect** templates colocated with the primitive (e.g. `*.figma.ts` next to the component) **or** record variant/slot parity in **`docs/design-system/governance.md`** in the **same** change when no Code Connect file exists yet.
4. Update `lib/design-system.ts` schemas / parsers if new variants are added.

## Before adding a new component via Figma workflows

- Run `search_design_system` — reuse an existing primitive before creating a new one.
- Do not introduce a Figma component that has no code counterpart; they must stay in sync.

## Palette discipline (non-negotiable)

- Never introduce hardcoded palette colors in primitives to satisfy a Figma mock.
- Convert to a semantic token in `app/globals.css` first, then reference the token in both code and Figma.
